KEYS
----

Alt ←            Insert the current objectb in the command line.
Alt p            Returns previous executed command line.
Alt t            Change panel listing mode (’Standard’,’Brief’,’Full’).
Alt i            Change inactive panel directory to the current directory on the active panel.
Alt n            Returns next executed command line.
Alt a            Sends pwd command execution result to the command line (current directory full path).
Alt c            Call menu for quick current directory change on active panel.
Alt Shift h      Call recently executed commands history.
Ins              Highlight current objectb.
Ctrl \           Call often used directories menu.
Shift F1         Call menu for fast jump between mount points on the left panel.
Shift F2         Call menu for fast jump between mount points on the right panel.
F3               File view.
Shift F3         Raw ﬁle view discarding extension.
Shift F4         Create new ﬁle.
Ctrl o           Hide panels.
Ctrl s           Fast search for ﬁle or directory.
Ctrl T           Insert
Ctrl Space       Show current directory size.
Ctrl x + t       Insert all highlighted objects into the command line.
Ctrl x + c       View/edit current object’sb permissions.
Ctrl x + o       View/edit current object’sb owner/group.
Ctrl x + l       Create hard link for the current objectb.
Ctrl x + s       Create symbolic link for the current objectb.
Ctrl x + Ctrl s  Edit symlink.
Ctrl x + j       Show all background jobs.
Ctrl x + q       Quick ﬁle view on another panel.
Ctrl x + i       Quick info about current objectb on another panel.
Ctrl v           Cycle through display mode for spaces and/or tabs.
Meta ?           Call extended ﬁle search menu.
Meta o           Change inactive panel directory to one pointed at active panel.
Meta .           Show/hide hidden ﬁles or directories (ﬁles with prepending dot).
Meta ,           Change panel display mode (vertically/horizontally).
Meta i           Disables ”Returns does autoindent” in mcedit, useful for preformatted text in-serting from the buffer.
Alt = Esc
Esc + 2 = F2